rComments: BV is a nice guy, but not a great prof. His lectures were difficult to follow and his handwriting is borderline illegible. He has a tendency to finish sentences in whispers. The exams were difficult but not impossible. BV expects his students to have a certain level of maturity. Don't take this course unless required.

Valko concentrated far too much on theory and not enough practical examples. His final exam was impossible. Sadly, probably the best 234 professor I could have taken. He's a great guy, just a very average professor.

The lectures are brutal. You can't understand the guy and he's incredibly dull. Sure, math is pretty boring to begin with, but math plus him is a dangerous combination. Only take this course if you have to.
